                <opener>
                    <placeName>New York</placeName>
                    <date>Feby 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1876</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>We have charged your account with half cost of the old plates of “Variation of Plants &amp; Animals” from Messrs Judd &amp; Co. in accordance with our arrangement. When may we expect the plates of the new edition?<ref target="#foot.f1"/> We had hoped that “Insectivorous Plants” would have sold better, but there has great depression in business during the last year &amp; the sale of all books has decreased very much.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours very truly | D. Appleton &amp; Co.</p>
<p><lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esqre <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p>Sales by D Appleton &amp; Co to Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> /76 of “<hi rend="doubleUnderline">Origin of Species</hi>” for use of Cha<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> Darwin</p>
